                <h1>Who Invented the Pina Colada?</h1>
                <p>The Pina Colada, a tropical cocktail, was created in the 1950s in Puerto Rico. The exact inventor is often debated, but bartender Ramón "Monchito" Marrero claims to have developed it in 1954 at the Caribe Hilton Hotel. Made from rum, coconut cream, and pineapple juice, this drink has become a symbol of paradise and relaxation.</p>
